fields.Title: WESTCOAST / EXECUTIONS VISCAL
fields.Description: An easy PERCEPTION check highlights a scattering of bullet holes in the wall. Pass a medium VISUAL CALCULUS and the interact appears as a ghostly mass execution perpetrated by dotted lines against a row of figures facing the wall. Either way, dialogue with the object has you and Lt Kitsuragi figure out it was an execution after the amphibious assault. You may relive it as an INLAND EMPIRE dream sequence later.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Hmm, correct." The lieutenant exam..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Hmm, correct." The lieutenant examines the wall closely. "The density of the bullet holes is unusual, even in a general *average bullet hole frequency in Martinaise* sense. Grim affairs."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "The lieutenant gives a terse nod. "..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lieutenant gives a terse nod. "Nothing for us to do here. Let's move along."

fields.Title: Endurance: "Phew! All that nodding was rough on..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Phew! All that nodding was rough on the old neck. Close to feeling that twinge...

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "The lieutenant matches your nodding..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lieutenant matches your nodding pace. He's a true professional at this.

fields.Title: Esprit de Corps: "You, your friends, your family. Eve..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You, your friends, your family. Everyone you had ever known. This was *you*.

fields.Title: Esprit de Corps: "Leeches, fleas, and thieves. All th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Leeches, fleas, and thieves. All the freeloader scum living off the hard work of others. Such is your belief.

fields.Title: You: "Look at the people against the wall..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Look at the people against the wall.

fields.Title: Esprit de Corps: "Follow your brother into death itse..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Follow your brother into death itself.

fields.Title: Empathy: "Maybe you should change it. They we..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Maybe you should change it. They were praying... screaming...

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "The commandant -- the one who gives..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The commandant -- the one who gives the order. Machine gun fire crackling through the air, the lights of the muzzle flashes dancing on his face...

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Meaning, this is *a lot* of bullet..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Meaning, this is *a lot* of bullet holes." He brushes the wall with his hand. "Looks like fully-automatic rifle fire. Something you don't see these days..."

fields.Title: Endurance: "Abort! Abort! No... shit, it's too..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Abort! Abort! No... shit, it's too late!

fields.Title: Endurance: "Whew, got off really lucky... that..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Whew, got off really lucky... that could have resulted in a world of hurt.

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "The sun blazes high up in the sky....."
fields.Dialogue Text: The sun blazes high up in the sky... baking the planks, the sand, your skin. The order was carried out in the afternoon.

fields.Title: Authority: "Soldiers... people in a bad spot th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Soldiers... people in a bad spot they probably did not choose, ordered to commit acts they wanted no part of.

fields.Title: Logic: "Remember what Trant Heidelstam said..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Remember what Trant Heidelstam said about Feld.

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "A long time has passed since the mo..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A long time has passed since the moment of this fusillading. Rain and brine have since washed all the blood away. Not a trace remains.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Another likely scenario." The lieu..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Another likely scenario." The lieutenant nods.

fields.Title: You: "I'm dumb."
fields.Dialogue Text: I'm dumb.

fields.Title: You: "Why this many bullet holes?"
fields.Dialogue Text: Why this many bullet holes?
fields.tooltip2: Bullet holes in the back yard.

fields.Title: Perception (Sight): "The density and spread of these bul..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The density and spread of these bullet holes is surprising -- this takes *a lot* of bullets. Fully-automatic rifle fire.

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "A row of ghostly shades facing a cr..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A row of ghostly shades facing a crumbling wall, with another seven shades standing ten metres from them. A single person stands on the sideline.

fields.Title: Physical Instrument: "It's too much! You can feel your ve..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's too much! You can feel your vertebrae starting to crack, your muscles groaning...

fields.Title: Endurance: "Whew, got off lucky there... that c..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Whew, got off lucky there... that could have resulted in a world of hurt.

fields.Title: You: ""What if it was the Feld personnel..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What if it was the Feld personnel when their assets were being seized by the revolutionaries?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Perhaps the ones executed here wer..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Perhaps the ones executed here were the loyalist-conservatives -- killed by the communists at the start of the civil war. Or it could have been the communists, put to death during the last stretch of the conflict by the Coalition forces."

fields.Title: Perception (Sight): "A scattering of bullet holes is spr..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A scattering of bullet holes is spread across the cracked wall, reaching from one corner to the other.

fields.Title: You: "Who was who in this execution? I ne..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Who was who in this execution? I need to understand.
fields.Alternate1: "Kim, who was who in this execution?"

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "The lieutenant is nodding so hard i..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lieutenant is nodding so hard it looks like his head is about to snap off his neck.

fields.Title: You: ""OH SHIT FUCK HELL!""
fields.Dialogue Text: "OH SHIT FUCK HELL!"

fields.Title: Authority: "In all truth, violence offers no an..."
fields.Dialogue Text: In all truth, violence offers no answer... It's only the last available resort when all mediation fails. And here, all did fail.

fields.Title: You: "Who were they?"
fields.Dialogue Text: Who were they?

fields.Title: Esprit de Corps: "Ordinary people -- familiar, each a..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Ordinary people -- familiar, each and every one of them.

fields.Title: You: ""Oh my god, look at all these bulle..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Oh my god, look at all these bullet holes! I haven't seen any other bullet holes in the walls before, somehow."

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "Ten metres away -- other shades are..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Ten metres away -- other shades are lined up in an orderly manner, automatic rifles primed. A gust of wind blows by -- the coats of the firing squad flap slowly in the breeze. A single person stands on the side.

fields.Title: Esprit de Corps: "Two officers of the law against the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Two officers of the law against the world. Nodding in unison. It is your source of power. The bond of camaraderie between you... is palpable...

fields.Title: You: "Don't stop nodding."
fields.Dialogue Text: Don't stop nodding.

fields.Title: Esprit de Corps: "He would follow you into death itse..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He would follow you into death itself... and you would do the same for him.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Alright," the lieutenant coughs ab..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Alright," the lieutenant coughs abruptly. "It's a good moment to stop. My neck was starting to hurt. If there's nothing more, we should get going."

fields.Title: Authority: "Overpriced mercenaries putting down..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Overpriced mercenaries putting down some rabid dogs. Someone's gotta do it, right?

fields.Title: You: ""You mentioned Coalition forces. Co..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "You mentioned Coalition forces. Could it have been them against the wall?"

fields.Title: You: "Walk away. [Leave.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: Walk away. [Leave.]

fields.Title: You: "Even more bullet holes. Something h..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Even more bullet holes. Something has definitely happened here.
fields.Alternate1: "Look, Kim. Even more bullet holes. Something's definitely gone down here."

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "A host of men, probably in everyday..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A host of men, probably in everyday clothes -- ragged from the conflict and covered in dust. They were not sitting (a common practice for executions in some nations), as demonstrated by the height level of the bullet holes.

fields.Title: You: ""Why not?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Why not?"

fields.Title: Perception (Sight): "The scattering of bullet holes look..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The scattering of bullet holes looks like one giant smiling mouth. Smiling its deadly smile.

fields.Title: You: "Nod even more."
fields.Dialogue Text: Nod even more.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "He nods in agreement -- it really i..."
fields.Dialogue Text: He nods in agreement -- it really is a very serious scene, worth shaking your head over.

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "The sun falls slowly toward the hor..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The sun falls slowly toward the horizon... the last light of the day. The order was carried out in the evening.

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "Droplets of rain fall on the wooden..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Droplets of rain fall on the wooden planks, the surrounding sand dunes. The clouds block out any rays of light...

fields.Title: Reaction Speed: "Or maybe..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Or maybe...

fields.Title: Esprit de Corps: "Collateral damage on the path towar..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Collateral damage on the path toward normalcy and progress. Such is your belief, officer.

fields.Title: You: ""What about people from the Coaliti..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "What about people from the Coalition? The so-called moralists?"

fields.Title: You: "Shake your head."
fields.Dialogue Text: Shake your head.

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "It's dark, very dark... faint light..."
fields.Dialogue Text: It's dark, very dark... faint lights flicker at the edge of your vision. It's rare for the order to be carried out at night...

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "A row of ghostly shades stand facin..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A row of ghostly shades stand facing the wall. There are many of them, a dozen at least, their heads lowered and eyes blindfolded. It's quiet. No sound, no movement.

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "Unable to piece together the *big p..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Unable to piece together the *big picture* just now. There's a hole in the hypothesis.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Yeah... it's very unlikely the Coa..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Yeah... it's very unlikely the Coalition forces were the ones who died here. They were always the *last* ones against the wall."

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "Seven men in combat uniforms and da..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Seven men in combat uniforms and dark coats, holding automatic rifles aimed at the people. Soldiers from some side... but from which one?

fields.Title: You: "Keep nodding, goddamn it! Stay the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Keep nodding, goddamn it! Stay the course!

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""The manufacturing and sale of auto..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "The manufacturing and sale of automatic rifles was curtailed after the Revolution. The destructive power of such tools proved to be... too much. We do need to retain some humanity in this world."

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "A small bead of sweat runs down the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A small bead of sweat runs down the side of the lieutenant's face as he maintains his nodding...

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Busted the neck, did you?" He cran..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Busted the neck, did you?" He cranes his neck left and right, stretching. "Glad I stopped when I did... my neck was really starting to hurt. Don't worry, it'll mend... now, we should get going."

fields.Title: You: "Look at the person standing on the..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Look at the person standing on the side.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""It could even have been the employ..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "It could even have been the employees of the Feld R&D Center down the coast, as their building was taken over by the revolutionaries."

fields.Title: You: "Fine. Okay."
fields.Dialogue Text: Fine. Okay.

fields.Title: Perception (Sight): "The scattering of bullet holes look..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The scattering of bullet holes looks like one giant smiling mouth. Smiling its deadly smile. Laughing at you and the world and the living.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""To be honest, if a Coalition membe..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "To be honest, if a Coalition member was anyone in this situation -- it was the commandant. The superior giving the orders."

fields.Title: Authority: "Men of duty. Dark duty."
fields.Dialogue Text: Men of duty. Dark duty.

fields.Title: Authority: "Martyrs of the Nation, the ardent k..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Martyrs of the Nation, the ardent knights. The few who had the guts to do this.

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "I'm just a representation of your m..."
fields.Dialogue Text: I'm just a representation of your mental faculties... piecing together any available information. You should probably ask the lieutenant.

fields.Title: You: "Good bye. [Leave.]"
fields.Dialogue Text: Good bye. [Leave.]

fields.Title: You: ""Kim, who was who in this execution?""
fields.Dialogue Text: "Kim, who was who in this execution?"

fields.Title: Endurance: "The nodding's reaching critical mas..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The nodding's reaching critical mass! You can't take this much longer, captain!

fields.Title: Pain Threshold: "Almost snapped your neck... but I f..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Almost snapped your neck... but I fucking got this. No pain... no pain...

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "They stand, facing the wall... It's..."
fields.Dialogue Text: They stand, facing the wall... It's impossible to discern any details about their personality or background.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "At first the lieutenant doesn't say..."
fields.Dialogue Text: At first the lieutenant doesn't say a word... he just stares at the wall. "I don't know," he says finally. "I don't know who died here, lined up beside that horrible wall. It could have been any of the parties involved in the Revolution."

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "A cold sea wind blows away the figu..."
fields.Dialogue Text: A cold sea wind blows away the figures.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Alright," the lieutenant coughs ab..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Alright," the lieutenant coughs abruptly. "I'm glad we stopped when we did... my neck was starting to hurt. If there's nothing more, we should get going."

fields.Title: You: "Who were they?"
fields.Dialogue Text: Who were they?

fields.Title: Authority: "Murderers. Twisted by orders. Young..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Murderers. Twisted by orders. Young boys forced into killing.

fields.Title: Shivers: "Behind this building -- the other o..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Behind this building -- the other one. Once filled with engineers and designers of Feld Electric, now collapsed and dead, but for some rats... You feel drawn, for some reason, to the faded mural again.

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "The abundance of bullet holes leads..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The abundance of bullet holes leads to two options: either an inordinate amount of executions were performed here, or they did not use a *conscience round* -- where only one soldier has the loaded rifle. Looks like this was a mass execution with everyone fully armed.

fields.Title: You: "Look at the line of soldiers."
fields.Dialogue Text: Look at the line of soldiers.

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "The morning sun rises beyond the ho..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The morning sun rises beyond the horizon, radiating the first light of the day. The order was carried out at dawn.

fields.Title: You: "What *is* this..."
fields.Dialogue Text: What *is* this...

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "The lieutenant also nods. It is qui..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The lieutenant also nods. It is quite a scene -- the two of you standing next to the broken wall of an abandoned building... nodding. Nodding along.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: "As the lieutenant takes out a handk..."
fields.Dialogue Text: As the lieutenant takes out a handkerchief and softly taps the sweat off his temple... a faint crack echoes through the coast...

fields.Title: Visual Calculus: "Snowflakes fall on the wooden plank..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Snowflakes fall on the wooden planks and the surrounding sand dunes, covering the land with the white of innocence...

fields.Title: You: "Say nothing, just nod."
fields.Dialogue Text: Say nothing, just nod.

fields.Title: Endurance: "Your neck couldn't withstand all th..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Your neck couldn't withstand all this effort... it's too much!

fields.Title: You: "Just one more nod."
fields.Dialogue Text: Just one more nod.

fields.Title: Esprit de Corps: "Comrades. The forsaken, the wretche..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Comrades. The forsaken, the wretched, who tried to rise against the horrors of the world.

fields.Title: Esprit de Corps: "Foreign dissidents, unwashed crimin..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Foreign dissidents, unwashed criminals, and hoi polloi. Such is your belief, officer.

fields.Title: You: "Stop nodding."
fields.Dialogue Text: Stop nodding.
